Git can keep track of changes in our project.

Git can remember:

  what files changed

  when they changed
  
  who changed them
  
  old versions of the project



Create a project folder. Make a new folder called myproject.

  mkdir myproject

Go inside the folder. Move into the myproject folder.

  cd myproject

Start Git in that folder. Turn this folder into a Git repository.

  git init

  After this, Git creates a hidden folder called:

    .git

    That hidden folder stores the project’s Git history.
